/node_modules
/data
/package-lock.json
# dist/ and dist-esm/ are intentionally tracked. CAW's frontend imports
# smltxt as a file: dependency from this directory, and vite resolves
# the package via its main / exports entries (dist/src/index.js,
# dist-esm/src/index.js). Operators installing CAW shouldn't need to
# build smltxt themselves — keeping the built artifacts in git makes
# every install reproducible without an extra toolchain step.
# Rebuild and re-commit when src/ changes:
#   cd smltxt && npm install && npm run build